	   <tr><td colspan=2>Going with your not-the-most-buff warrior/SK type, i created an erudite shadowknight, of which i only know 1 on my server that is over level 50. It is probably the least played class, even less so than erudite pallys for some reason even though erudites do have very nice int for shadow-knight-ly purposes :) I am now lvl 22 with her and its sweet :) So to sum up i dont think stats matter as much as long as you have fun with the character youre playing and youre not playing in effect someone else's character by spending all your points on what other people recommend you to spend them on. Same goes for armour and weapons. Just my view on things<br>&nbsp;<br>Venchantra Everbreeze<br>Enchantress of the 59th level<br>Venshado Vivisection<br>Erudite Dark-knight of 48th level<br></td></tr>
