	   <tr><td colspan=2>Starting stats are not as important as one might think, although not saying that they aren't either.&nbsp;&nbsp;There are alot of items to boost any stat you really want, at a price anyway.  I have a level 32 SK and I have him pretty twinked out for my level.  I have a fbss and a wurmslayer. I deal heavy damage, but miss quite often.  To do it all over again I would have put more points into my dex, because there are alot of str items, and we also recieve decent buffs for str.  Dex items however I have very few of.  To spred out your points evenly though I don't know about.  I agree don't spread your points so thin.  And I would highly disagree in putting points in Charm.  Shadow Knights aren't known as your knight's in shinny armor, that's a Pally.  But if you want a beautiful knight, that's what's great about RPG. You can't be wrong.  But low charisma helps your fear spells, well so i've heard.  <br><br>Scyinide<br>32 Shadow Knight<br>Tallon Zek Server<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
